This paper deals with semantics of logic programs, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses approximation fixpoint theory, which is a common technique used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the use of minimal models, which is a topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and the iterative procedure used in the paper can be seen as a form of algorithm design, which is a topic in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
